The United States has expressed its support for the Venezuelan people's fight for democracy, freedom, and the rule of law. They condemn the actions of President Maduro, whom they accuse of trying to become a dictator. The US has threatened to take strong economic actions if Maduro proceeds with his plan to impose a Constituent Assembly on July 30. The US also calls for free and fair elections and pledges to stand with the people of Venezuela in their efforts to restore their country to a prosperous democracy.